layers.description: This metadata describes the stereocompiled Edge of Pavement (EOP) polygons feature of DRCOG Denver Region Urbanized Project Area. The feature was compiled from the Denver Regional Aerial Photography Project (DRAPP) 2014 Aerial Imagery Acquisition and Production. This 1"=100' scale imagery is comprised of 4-band RGBIR color orthoimagery with a GSD (Ground Sample Distance) of 0.5'. Imagery was collected with the Leica ADS40 and ADS80 digital sensors and processed with Leica XPro software. Imagery is projected in State Plane Coordinate System, Colorado central zone using the Lambert Conformal Conic map projection parameters. Horizontal and vertical datums are NAD83(11) and NAVD88(GEOID12A) respectively.

Floodplain delineations in this feature class are dissolved and merged based FLOODPLAIN, FEMAZONE, ADOPTYR, DRAINAGE. Where they exist, "Shallow", 10-, 25-, 50-, and 200-Year floodplains are also delineated. All delineations were compiled from feature classes in the City's PROD1 database in February and March of 2018. Data from "snapshots" in 2003, 2006, 2009, and 2012 were copied and re-attributed. There are no duplicate geometries within this dataset. Notably, no snapshots existed for High Hazard and Conveyance Zones in 2012. layers.description: The Parks and Recreation natural lands Weeds Points database is part of the tracking system to record and report specific species numbers and locations for certain species categoried as Noxious or invasive in the Integrated Pest Management program. Weeds termed "Noxious" are listed by the Colorado Department of Agriculture as A-List, B-List, C-List, and Watch-List and have corresponding control initiatives based on the category. Other invasive weed species may be mapped based on program needs and species threat to ecosystem health.
